    • Method Detail

      • dependencySource

        @NotNull
B dependencySource(boolean value)
        Setting true means that method RichPageWidget.processParameterDependencies(RichPageWidgetDependenciesContext) should be called on server after this parameter value was changed by user on the client side.

        It is supported for a parameter to be both dependency source and target.
        Since:
        3.9.2
        See Also:
        dependencyTarget(boolean)

      • dependencyTarget

        @NotNull
B dependencyTarget(boolean value)
        Setting true means that this parameter is depending on some other parameter(s) and it's configuration will be set in method RichPageWidget.processParameterDependencies(RichPageWidgetDependenciesContext). Changes done in that method to parameters which were not marked as dependency target by calling this method with 'true' are silently ignored.

        It is also used to visually indicate to the user that some processing is being done on the server.

        It is supported for a parameter to be both dependency source and target.
        Since:
        3.9.2
        See Also:
        dependencySource(boolean)
